:: Case 3 introduction 

Stéphanie is a 15-year-old teenage girl who lives in XXXXX TODO and comes to the hospital saying that she felt like she was suffocating during the night because of coughing and cannot sleep without 2 pillows for at least two weeks. She also has chest pain. 

She has been sweating more than usual (do we mention fever? TODO) and pain in her right knee, more than the left, for two days. After being asked, she remembers she had pain in her arm joints (elbows and shoulders) but she felt better with diclofenac, as well as having a recent throat cold. 

After trying everything she could, her best friend convinced her to come to the hospital in case there were medications that could help her.

