:: Treatment 3
The mitral valve showed thickened cusps with commissural fusion and reduced opening, compatible with mitral stenosis due to severe rheumatic heart disease. The maximum diastolic gradient between the left atrium and the ventricle was estimated at 29 mm Hg, and the mean at 16 mm Hg; the aortic valve appears to function normally. The systolic pressure of the pulmonary artery was estimated at 50 mmHg.
